'''Mukul S. Anand''' ([[11 October]], [[1951]] - [[7 September]] [[1997]]) was an [[Indian film]] writer, producer and director. He was the nephew of veteran film scriptwriter ''[[Inder Raj Anand]]'' and cousin of actor and director [[Tinnu Anand]].

His most notable films included ''[[Sultanat]]'' (1986), ''[[Agneepath]]'' (1990), ''[[Hum (film)|Hum]]'' (1991) and ''[[Khuda Gawah]]'' (1992).

He died of a [[heart attack]] at the age of 45 in September [[1997]]. At the time of his death he was in the middle of filming the movie ''[[Dus (1997 film)|Dus]]'' which was left incomplete after his death and never released. Promo videos and clips from what was shot of the film can be seen on his official website.

